The paper analyzes the discriminant power of different centrality indices, which is a topic related to social network analysis and graph theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper uses empirical analysis and proposes new conjectures, which suggests a focus on data analysis and theoretical research, respectively. This could lead to categorization in sub-categories such as cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.SD (Software Development), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
